description._content: Catalog #: 15_000140 Title: Charles M. Daniels Collection Photo Aircraft/Subject: Bell P-39Q Airacobra Daniels Album Name: Garber Facility, Smithsonian, '86 Notes From Album: Bell P-39Q-15-BE Airacobra, sn 44-2433, Allison V-1710-86 Additional Information: Flown by Earl Oldman in the 1946 National Air Races. Sold to Elizabeth Haas later that year. Named ""Galloping Gertie"" and was flown in air races and shows. Donated to the National Air & Space Museum in 1965. Registered as N57591. Underwent restoration and is now displayed at the Niagra Air & Space Museum in Niagra Falls, NY. Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
